RACE.FOOTNOTES: HARRY HOOD set the pace along the inside, showed the way from an outer presser around the far turn, shook free while shifting out to the three path straightening for home and held sway thereafter. BABA VOSS laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, displayed good courage by splitting rivals through a narrow seam in upper stretch, vied for place with an outer rival in the final furlong, tipped outside of the clear leader in the closing stages, but did not have enough to offer a bid while securing second. BRIGADE COMMANDER pursued from midpack two wide, took closer order before chasing outside of the top pair from within striking around into the far turn, took aim on the clearing leader from the four path in upper stretch, but lacked the needed kick to offer a bid and got outfinished by an inner rival for place. NOISES OFF laid in midpack along the inside, awaited racing room behind traffic nearing the lane, altered course outwardly in upper stretch to be four wide entering the final furlong, and stayed on between horses. MO SATURDAYS settled well back along the inside, moved between horses at the half mile pole, took the far turn in the two to three path before swinging to the five path and between foes entering the lane, but only offered a mild kick. NOW THAT ICAN ROCK laid off of the pace three to four wide, fanned to the six path entering the lane and lacked the needed kick to offer a bid. BOONE'S PATH stalked two wide, prompted outside of the pace setter around the far turn, but lost place to an outer rival entering the lane, and gave way between horses. CREATIVE WAY tracked along the inside, but caved entering the final furlong. TESTIMONY TIME laid off of the pace along the inside, but checked entering the far turn, trailed soon after, then steadied along the inside in upper stretch. DAI VERNON was slow into stride and trailed early on, moved out of last in the three path around the far turn, but floated to the seven path entering the lane and failed to factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUMMERTIME ROSE bumped an outer rival at the fifteen sixteenths pole, opened up a wide margin down the backstretch, came back to the field around the far turn, met an outer challenge entering the lane and held sway. PADDY GAL took contact from an inner rival passing the fifteen sixteenths pole, pursued from midpack along the inside, was roused for gain leaving the three furlong pole, took aim outside of the leader nearing the lane, offered a bid entering it, but was turned away in upper stretch and fended off thereafter. AUTISM COMMUNITY broke outwardly, pursued three wide, but weakened turning for home before being floated to the seven path entering the lane. MALIBU SMART bobbled outwardly at the start, lacked speed in the four path, but was through at the five furlong pole, eased while detaching from the rest around the far turn, got pulled up in upper stretch before being escorted back to her handlers by an out-rider and walked off.
